content: Relaxing fun for about the right amount of time. Recommended!
Really nice and peaceful space trader, works well, even on lower end chromebooks. Well worth the price
Excellent game. It's a simple Elite-style space game with all of the annoying stuff taken out. It has a really nice rewarding progression and I eagerly await any future expansions.
It's fun, and a cool concept. But it gets repetitive after an hour or two.

Really enjoyed my time with this game. Its like a mix of Elite and Freelancer without any annoying battles or deaths. I enjoyed it so much that I had to get all of the achievements (that last million took me a few days!). The gameplay loop of trading, exploring, upgrading is really compelling and its all done in a totally chilled envoronment. No in-app purchases and adverts makes this game just that much better. Thanks for creating this.

Has potential but far from a game, feels like a student's project. 1. Add a story (even a hint on a plot will help). Why am i trading to get a better class ship? Lame! 2. Interface needs lots of work, why not add Sell All or Buy Max buttons, etc? 3. Add variety to merchendise and races as well as description to flash out the universe. Things like that. Otherwise good effort, but not quite there yet.

Lovely graphics, sounds and intuitive controls. Like a polished, modern cross between Damocles and Elite. It's a short experience (as advertised) but very enjoyable and I still play it to trade and fly about in space because it's so much fun and looks so pretty. Would love to see our galaxy added and escort or passenger missions included. Also be nice to come across other ships here and there in space. Well worth the money and no ads or tricks make it a terrific game to chill-out with.

Very relaxing and fun to explore, it's all I've ever looked for in a space themed game. I would love for there to be an update with new galaxies and ships, since I finished the game in around 2 or 3 days. Of course, I still have a few achievements to still get, I'd just love to explore more worlds is all, but no pressure. It's not a must have, just a nice little add on that would be much appreciated
fantastic space trading game, could do with some form of combat perhaps
It's a fun game and I like it a lot. Was hoping it would have a bit more to it. Found all the sectors to quick. It was fun while I was playing it.

Nice space trading game.. Like original Elite brought up to modern standards but with less fighting. I would love a way of seeing a log of buy/sell amounts without having to use a pen and paper outside of the app, but I still give it 5 stars.
brilliant so far!
Unfortunately doesn't work on the Tesco hudl 2. (An Intel Atom based Android 5.1, Lollipop tablet from 2014) Opens to black full screen, then immediately closes.
Great experience. I'm having a blast just going from planet to planet. Hoping the dev can expand the amount of systems. Full PVE is nice, too. A nice, relaxing time sink.
I like it.
This is a really good game, I got it on sale for 99 cents. It is worth 4 dollars anyway. Super fun
Super chill game, I had a blast just running cargo and not getting blown up. Only thing I want is more content or an end game galaxy. Great job dev!

content: I supported one time purchase games and this game is cool ! Sci-fi fans don't miss out ***Add camera mode pls***
Great game! Casual and relaxing.
I really love this game! It's so peaceful and refreshing from all the other space fighting games. I wish there was more to do.

A wonderful game, beautifully made as well as reasonably priced. While still being a simple trading type role-playing game in which you visit multiple locations to buy or sell goods at varying prices, it sets itself apart from many other similar games with it's open world sandbox.W ould have made this a five star if there was more to landing and exploring planets; being able to stay on one planet and trade between several NPCs maybe. Awesome game, still.

Great game considering the quality put out from a one man designe team. Only criticism I have is that the sources used to label extraterrestrial life as "Aliens" is outdated, secular, and uneducated in the occult/religion fields of study. Their demons masquerading as higher entities. Do your research on your next game. Change that or add a backstory that explains out your oversight and the game would be 5 stars.
Really great game
Fun. Simple. Calming. Focus on discovering the best trade routes and maximize profits selling whatever you get your hands on. Could use some expanding, but I like the basic game where it is.
Has potential, needs more to do at start. Otherwise very easy to control and beautifully made.
Pretty cool 👍
Stellar little space trading game.
very fun, if a bit small
Very easy to get on to.
Awesome game if new contents being made thats just a bonus.
Phenomenonal game for such small expense. If u liked Galaxy on fire without the conflict then this is for u

I typically require conflict to be the motivating source of challenge in a game, but this one has a charm that reminds me of the safe shallows of Subnautica. I am so busy with discovery that I never miss the combat. Great for passing time when need to kill a few minutes, but the ambiance and nicely paced rewards can easily have you wondering where the hours went.
I'm having fun playing this game. I love exploring and trading. Perfect game for me.
Can't fault this really considering its made by one guy. The game play loop isn't the worst and a tad repetitive but it's relaxing and well made. Kudos!!

This is such a great game! I played this back on my old Palm T3. It was an addictive and fun game both then and now. I wish there were more star systems to explore and having the risk of running into space cops while carrying weapons or narcotics would be fun.

I was pretty exited to buy a peaceful space game. But this game also contains elements of magic that are not alluded to in the description of the game. TBF it was visible on a screenshot but I didn't notice it. Kind of weirdly out of genre and I just don't like to play that sort of game. Anyhow. This is a no for me.

Cute, addictive, and relaxing. Although it can get a little repetitive after a while and I wish there was more to *do.* But I respect the fact that it's made by one person, it ain't easy making a game, so right on. Idk if this exists in the game already, but it would be nice to be able to see what kind of cargo each planet/civilization is willing to buy right from your map - so if you have a bunch of stuff to sell, you're not flying everywhere guessing where to go to sell each item you have.
Calming. I can see the effort you put into it. Good job and I enjoy playing.
short but good. looking forward to the next major update.

I found the game to be really good, the graphics were good a d it had a very easy to follow storyline, my only comment would be that the game is quite short, but outside of that it's an excellent game.

Overall, this game is very simplistic and relaxing, and it should stay that way. All you do here is basically trade with different planets in their stellar systems, which you can unlock by buying star system shards/pieces, and travel through the unlocked systems to trade more, and buy new ships. The game is overall fantastic as it is, but there is one problem, which is the disappearing use of the system shards after unlocking the available systems. That aside, great job! Would recommend.
Great game, very intriguing design.
Great game for chilling out
Wonderful ❤️ The perfect mobile game, no hidden fees, no adverts. Well worth the small cost.
it costs 69p and thats nice
Relaxing fun
Best mobile space flight game out there hands down
It is interesting, for the first 5 minutes, and than very repetitive and boring.
Very calm game. Entertaining for hours. No ads or Microtransactions.
You think it's one type of game and it's another type of game. Get it you'll like it call
Exactly as advertised.

This is a wonderful game and an outstanding achievement for its developer! I appreciate there being no micro transactions or waiting. It's worth more than the asking price! Edit: Additionally, I haven't encountered any bugs!
Really fun game, good way to sink a few hours even if it's a little short. For a one man effort though it's very impressive.
I Rate it 5 Star 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟 Simple as that! I LOVE IT! ❤ HF Games give us more about the game. 😎
Really Good, simple but effective, great for just having fun, 100% recommended.

At last an open space trading game. I an really loving this game. Just one thing I want to ask you, Can you make controls a little bit smaller, or can you give options like control size adjustments, so that one can enjoy open space view at large, as big controls are taking a lots of space of the galactic view one can enjoy. Please take a note on that. And also more systems . I am waiting for that.
replyContent: Thanks for the review! You actually can change the size of the controls in the current version. 'Settings' / 'UI Scale' will let you adjust the control and HUD size :)

content: It's like being a friendly ferengi

This game reminds me of No Man's Sky. You fly from planet to planet trading and that's it. There's no battles with pirates, missions, story lines, storms or resource management. Actually you can't even lose in this game. That being said, it is definitely up there in terms of the 3d graphics. The traveling is done in such a way that it doesn't take away from the experience but it isn't irritating. The only reason this scores so high is because this is a mobile game. If it were on the PC, 2/5

You can fly from planets to planets trading stuff. Near planets there is places of interest like moons, wrakages or abandoned satellites where you can get free cargo loot. I wish the was enemies to shoot at. So far I am enjoying the game.
Love it Just waiting for more updates😊
Good fun
Fun game. Im enjoying it
Simple, but Fantastic.
Unique. Cool. Relaxing.

Got this on sale, well worth the $1. It's pretty straightforward, you just explore and find planets that want stuff the other ones have and be a courier for $$. I've only just got the 2and ship but I'm hoping there are bigger ones further down the track. Downgraded a star as there's only 4 systems and then you're done, would be nice if it was procedurally generated.
Fun to pass the time for awhile
It's been a long time since I felt like I was playing a game that reminded me of Freelancer - this is definitely worth a purchase.
Simple good fun and great graphics. I hope more systems and ships get added in the future.
Boring
Great game

This game is very enjoyable and is exactly the kind of game that not many space games are, exploring systems, and planetary bodies is, basically if anyone played Stellaris, you're the science ship, surveying. Really hope there will be more systems, or another game just like this but more massive, open, and serious custom ships. Too bad can't have star trek ships without making paramount and cbs very angry lol.
Good game
Simple and beautiful, chill out, space trading game. Very nice.
I am thoroughly enjoying this game. There is no 'bug' navigating away from planets, just needs a bit of skill to achieve. Once you figure it out, it is easy. Wish there were more galaxies to explore!
Coolgame
I really enjoyed playing this game and hope the creators expand on it. Maybe a little randomization on prices, random comets in solar systems? I can't wait to see what comes next!
Good deal, great game, but unfortunately somewhat short, still worth the money though.

This game doesn't promise you the world, but what it does promise you it absolutely delivers on. I wish more mobile games were like this. No ads, premium currency or sales tactics. You cruise across a beautiful universe with relaxing music and the simple goal of making money, exploring and upgrading your ship.

This is a fantastic game! It's very easy to play. Lots of different ships to buy. An open world to explore. Unlimited fuel, lots of aliens. No combat, no ads, nothing to buy! I hope the developer releases new galaxies soon!
Nice space feel on the Android
Great Game. No issues. Hoping for more content.
Awesome game! Needs more star systems to explore.
Pretty nifty little trading game. It's quite fun. Thank you.
moar plz
Loving this. Great just flying around buying selling salvaging and exploring. Very relaxing.

Small but nice game. I love the trading aspect. Reminds me of privateer but no pirates or kilrathi. Dev did a good job with the red shift at light speed and distances between stars. The quick stop isn't realistic but I didn't mind that. If you like trading games, this one is worth a look.

The game is awesome the way you fly from planet to planet to trade is gold The best part is when you buy a new space craft and fly to other galaxy's ,solar systems that's just awesome I love the game But if you could add a store that we buy things with real money like coins space ships and more love the game. And could you add some new solar systems or galaxy's
Would be great if unlimited systems. 3 solar systems is too few. was a blast the short time I had.

Unplayable I want to support non micro transaction games. But this one repeatedly gets stuck in a glitch that keeps flying you back to the planet you just visited with no way of breaking the cycle. Nice idea but for such a basic game this is terrible.

I like the look, the sounds and the idea. controls are easy to learn. but it lacks things to do. automatically breaking near objects in space takes a bit of fun. no fuel or other things i need to care about. its always just from planet to planet buying and selling the same stuff. it feels like wasted potential. still a very solid game to skip some time
absolutely marvellous - great to relax to
Relaxing, short, perfect
Awesome game. My only complaint is that there are only three galaxies to explore, and there isn't much information given about the types of stars that makes them unique.
Simple, chill.
Its a fun trader/space sim with a great simple economy. Has a huge exploration side that is fun. Worth the few dollars it cost.
cool little game I like it a lot hopefully developer adds features soon even as it is its good
a fun game with lots of potential. more galaxies please :)
i love this type of game, and this phone game does not disapoint!
it is a bit slow when trying to go around planets but it is fun to explore such a large space
fun, pretty, needs more content
Took the best part of Freelancer and made a very relaxing way to pass some time. Great not being harassed by adds or pay to play mechanics. Would love to see a sequel. Highly recommend.
quick to learn with simple UI.
Polished and relaxing x
Very spacey and peacefully healing lol 👽
this game is fun and relaxing. worth every penny.

I'm absolutely enthralled by this game and it has sat on my wishlist for far too long! The only thing I could ever hope for is a touch of life to the galaxy and local multiplayer perhaps? Even without those two things this game is a work of art here. Easily worth the original price let alone sale price.
relaxing and fun to explore
Very relaxing (as stated by dev) and quite short but good considering how we buy/play/beat/delete games nowadays.

As a value proposition, no microtransactions and 2usd this is must buy for anyone who might even be slightly interested. My main issue is that to play well you'll need a pen and paper to make notes of where buys and sells what, because you can't remember it all. Which is a little ridiculous. Unless I'm missing something. But not having a database if previous goods means you waste a lot time with a full cargo hold, unless you have a photographic memory...

Its almost like having Freelancer on your mobile!! great game and idea. you really are onto something with this and think it will do well on mobile platform for years to come. it's just very short and feels kinda like its in alpha but it still gave me a good 10+ hours of fun exploring, trading and upgrading my ship until it was too repetitive. I'd love to see this game updated with lots more content.
Love the game I havent found anythingwrong so far i enjoy it all the time it was worth the money i spent on it
A perfect game for a relaxing experience. I find myself coming back to it often and I wish there was more.
Please add more planets and extra stuff

Fun game, not too taxing. Nice to pick up when you want to kill a little time, good job! could use a tip on scientist achievement and also i cant get master explorer for Gemini system, am i missing something??
I LOVE IT!
It's a great game. It just needs more galaxies.
Pefect! Elite with out the hassle of fighting
Awesomely amazing space trade sim!

as you very well know it's to much basically auto pilot with out it enabled when warping. that aspect needs to be loosened a bit. and overall great. this reminds me most of all clones first encounter for dos which is still one of the greats.
Cool relaxing game although gamepad support would be cool... Game works fine without it, though
Brilliant little Elite inspired game. Game controls and hud make the newtonianish physics easy to master. hopefully there is more to come!

Wished there was more content, but LOVED this game. I spent months waiting to use my Google Play gift card from Christmas and now I finally found a game that is actually enjoyable and unique enough to savor. Please make a sequel, I would buy it for nearly $7!!!
pretty comfy
I love this game so much! It's truely open-world, as promised. But I think you should create more systems and more diverge ships as well as cargo. Thank you for this wonderful game!
great game!
Good game, i like hyperjump visuals
A great little exploration and trading game. Hope to see more content added in the future.
Very much like the old Elite game but much simpler. Would loved to have been able to land manually and had a more detailed ship, but still very good game for mobile.
cant wait for more content
Great game. just need more content.
absolutely beautiful game awesome it's so smooth and runs very nicely. great job very creative. awesome work developers 👍👍👍👍👍👍👍

I think it's a good concept I'm not sure because I had to refund it immediately the first planet I arrive to I got stuck on the trading screen and could not exit I panicked and had to refund I spent a good five minutes trying to trade the water which I did and then I could not exit the trading screen
Just what I wanted, an addicting and relaxing Space Trader.
replyContent: Oh no! Sorry about that, I'll look into this issue asap. I haven't heard of it happening before. If you have any other info that might be helpful, email me at hunter@hforsyth.com, I'd really appreciate it. Would also be happy to give a refund if you'd like.

content: great game with a great look. very easy to play to kill time.

Very relaxing Space Trading game. Game can be short for some, but personally I enjoyed the game, and I was happy to purchase to support the developer as the game is a rare gem. If the game takes off for the developer, players may get an expansion in the future, and if not, it doesn't matter because the game is charming in its current format. Good luck to the developer, I really enjoyed playing the game. Thank you.

Simple, kind of relaxed explore and trade gameplay. Enjoying it so far, but some kind of indicator as to whether prices are high or low on a planet would be useful. At first, its kind of trial & error whether you're overpaying or getting a bargain. Overall, a chill game for a decent price so can't complain at all.
Very cool. Need more content

Mobile space sims are fairly rare, and this one is a wonderful, relaxing, chill-out type of thing that cuts right through the complexity that usually plagues the genre. There are times I wish there was asteroid mining or space stations or other pilots, but the lack of combat is unique and contributes a lot to this game's zen-like feel. It makes space travel feel less like a career and more like a casual hobby, which really makes it stand out!
Really relaxing and casual.  Great to pick up and play.  Looking forward to seeing more updates to the game in the future!
Really chill space exploration game. I like the different speeds of travel - gets across the sense of size without making you sit there for ages!
its like playing elite dangerous on the phone

Well done! *Refreshing* change of space exploration. Not a shoot 'em up. Graphics are very clean. Planets and stars are excellent artwork. I don't usually leave music on during games.. But in this case, it made the whole experience very Zen-like. Well worth the price. Thank you devs. Please make more... 😊

Game is very fun, and has excellent controls. The one significant downside is very little content. I assumed when I started the game, that after you warp to the third system that more systems would become available, but that is it. I purchased the best ship and explored everywhere in only a few hours. If more content is going to be released I would give this game 5 stars, but for the content that is available, it does not seem to be worth the purchase price.
I like the fact that this is an ogfline game with no pirates to deal with but the content is very limited. I completed all the accomplishments in a couple of days. Not worth the money.

Finally, a chilled out space trading game without constant pirates and missions stressing me out in order to advance. It would be cool to have a simple cockpit view for a little immersive feel, but the game is great as is. No IAP or ads...a REAL game I can actually own. Thanks for making this!👍

i enjoy space exploration games the fact that you explore planets and sell goods makes this really enjoyable no need to worry about other ship hunting you down. two things I'd like to see maybe an option to mine astroids or planets as other source of income and not sure if possible but maybe a cockpit view? other then that keep up the good work.
keeps kicking me out
replyContent: Hi there, I'm sorry to hear that. Do you mind emailing your order # to hunter@hforsyth.com so that I can issue you a refund? You should be able to find it in the order confirmation email that Google Play sends.

This game shows potential! And those discovered places remind me of skyrim.
I really liked exploring and finding new planets.
